<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a much-confused species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="303 - 319" publicationUrl="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, 1936. The Brazilian species of Selaginella. Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 40: 303 - 319, DOI: 10.1002/fedr.19360402005" title="The Brazilian species of Selaginella." url="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" volume="40" year="1936">Alston (1936)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized it under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenm" authorityYear="1887" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella dendricola" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jenman. 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, CF" journalOrPublisher="Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B21" refString="Reed, CF, 1965-1966. Index Selaginellarum. Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana 18: 1 - 287" title="Index Selaginellarum." volume="18" year="1965 - 1966">Reed (1965-1966)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species and, apparently, subsumed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bak" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella trifurcata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="trifurcata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella trifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under it. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bak" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella trifurcata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="trifurcata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella trifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spring" authorityYear="1840" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella muscosa" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="muscosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella muscosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Valdespino, IA" journalOrPublisher="The City University of New York, New York" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" refId="B32" refString="Valdespino, IA, 1995. A monographic revision of Selaginella P. Beauv. subgenus Heterostachys Baker in Central and South America. Doctoral Thesis. The City University of New York, New York" title="A monographic revision of Selaginella P. Beauv. subgenus Heterostachys Baker in Central and South America. Doctoral Thesis." year="1995">Valdespino (1995)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bak" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella trifurcata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="trifurcata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella trifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as conspecific but not the same species as, or closely related to, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spring" authorityYear="1840" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella muscosa" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="muscosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella muscosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981</bibRefCitation>
: 298) a possible inadvertent lectotypification for 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bak" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella trifurcata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="trifurcata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella trifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the sense outlined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Prado, J" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" publicationUrl="10.12705/643.29" refId="B20" refString="Prado, J, Hirai, RY, Moran, RC, 2015. [046-048] Proposals concerning inadvertent lectotypifications (and neotypifications). Taxon 64, 651 pp., DOI: 10.12705/643.29" title="[046 - 048] Proposals concerning inadvertent lectotypifications (and neotypifications)." url="10.12705/643.29" volume="64" year="2015">Prado et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, could be inferred. Furthermore, specimens of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Spruce 2535</emphasis>
at BR! and RB! [RB 168977] are mixed collections which I have determined as: a = 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenm" authorityYear="1887" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella dendricola" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and b = 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; J. M. Rankin" authorityYear="1981" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella calceolata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="calceolata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella calceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jermy &amp; Rankin, while the same collection at G! and P! [P04026284] is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenm" authorityYear="1887" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella dendricola" order="Selaginellales" pageId="15" pageNumber="108" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="108">Selaginella dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<pageBreakToken pageId="16" pageNumber="109" start="start">Another</pageBreakToken>
duplicate of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Spruce 2535</emphasis>
at P ([P01244267]-image!) was also determined by Cremers as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenm" authorityYear="1887" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella dendricola" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These nomenclatural and taxonomic matters will be further discussed in a separate paper (see comment about this under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hieron" authorityYear="1904" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella glazioviana" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella glazioviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its ovate-deltate lateral leaves, with midribs conspicuously hyaline and upper surfaces hispidulous with prickle- or tooth-like projections usually found submarginally, marginally, and apically along the basiscopic halves of the laminae, and median leaves orbiculate or broadly ovate-elliptic. 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with a species currently being described with the epithet of &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="2016" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="aculeatifolia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="aculeatifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">aculeatifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (Venezuela), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bak" authorityYear="1883" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella brevifolia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="brevifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella brevifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Colombia, Venezuela, and Brazil), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alston" authorityYear="1981" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella sandwithii" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="sandwithii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella sandwithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Alston (Guyana and French Guiana) form a closely related group of taxa referred as the &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Valdespino, IA" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" refId="B36" refString="Valdespino, IA, in press. Selaginella aculeatifolia (Selaginellaceae - Lycopodiophyta), a new hispidulous species from the foothills of Cerro Neblina, Venezuela. In: Nordic Journal of Botany." title="Selaginella aculeatifolia (Selaginellaceae - Lycopodiophyta), a new hispidulous species from the foothills of Cerro Neblina, Venezuela." volumeTitle="Nordic Journal of Botany." year="in press">Valdespino in press</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
